nt banker Jacob Rothschild and Australian investorKerry Packer valued at $21.6 billion.   The cashless offer would be financed mostly with borrowed money.</TEXT><DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A trickle of picket-line crossovers has become asteady stream since the Eastern Airlines pilots' leadershipdiscussed ending a 5-month-old strike, sources said, boostingmanagement efforts to rebuild without the unions.   In meetings beginning Sunday, striking pilots resoundinglyrejected proposals to go back to work. However, sources who didn'twant to be identified said Thursday the number of pilots crossingthe picket lines neared 600, up from 200 at the strike's beginningon March 4 and from 385 a week ago.</TEXT><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   The Dow Jones industrial average made a near-miss run at arecord high Thursday as the stock market kept climbing in turbulenttrading.   The Dow Jones average of 30 blue chips finished with a26.55-point gain at 2,712.63 after trading earlier in the day abovethe record closing high of 2,722.42 reached on Aug. 25, 1987.   Bond prices surged as the government completed its quarterlyrefunding auctions.   The dollar finished higher in domestic dealings after putting ina mixed performance overseas.   Grain and soybean futures advanced modestly; coffee futuresprices fell sharply; energy futures rose; precious metals werehigher; and livestock and meat futures were mixed.</TEXT></DOC>